    "summary": "I feel very strongly about creating a fair, equal and equally enjoyable work environment for everyone, regardless of one's gender, race, sexual orientation, background or other label. Creating a diverse workforce is not necessarily the goal in itself, however, creating an inclusive culture within our organisations is. Not to tick the box, but because I want to do what I can to contribute to a future where everyone is valued, respected and appreciated.\n\nBorn of Dutch parents, I grew up in Japan, Indonesia, Singapore and Malaysia and feel this has contributed to my wish for more understanding towards one another. It has also helped me in adapting quickly to new situations and being able to converse with all manners of people and making them feel at ease.\n\nMy strengths lie in presenting, facilitating and bringing people together. My areas of expertise are diversity & inclusion, unconscious bias training, intercultural management and inclusive leadership.",
