                    "description": "Do what you feel in your heart to be right- for you'll be criticized anyway. You'll be damned if you do, and damned if you don't. - Eleanor Roosevelt\n\n\nI am a Diversity & Inclusion trainer, consultant and keynote speaker. My speciality lies in D&I themes such as bias-training, inclusive leadership, intercultural communication, empowerment programs and mentoring & sponsoring programs. Prior to this I worked as Diversity Manager for EY. I feel strongly about creating a fair and equal working environment for everyone, regardless of gender, race, background, sexuality, age or whatever defines us. Creating a diverse workforce is not a goal in itself, but creating an inclusive organisational culture, especially within the corporate realm, is what I most love doing.\n\nOften asked to give keynotes, most recently in Moscow at the invitation of the Russian Diversity Association, at Rabobank for Coming Out Day, at Nike for their EMEA leadership team, at Deutsche Bank for their Inclusion Event, at EY for their Career Watch Program, Johnson & Johnson for their Women\u2019s Network Event, ABN AMRO Private banking for their mentoring program kick off and NN (Nationale Nederlanden) for their Diversity launch. Training and consultancy clients include various law firms such as De Brauw, Blackstone & Westbroek, consultancies as KPMG and Deloitte, various universities including Delft University of Technology, and various governmental organisations including the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and the ABD.",
